{{Quick Guide}}

==Details==
{{Quest details page|The Grand Tree}}

==Walkthrough==
===Getting started===
{{Needed|recommended=[[Teleportation]] methods to [[Tree Gnome Stronghold]] and [[Yanille]].}}
{{Checklist|
*Speak to [[King Shareen]] in the [[Grand Tree]] (Make sure you have two empty slots to start the quest). {{Chat option|1You seem worried, what's up?|2I'd be happy to help!}} Accept the quest to get a [[Translation book]] and a [[Bark sample]].
*Travel to the island east of [[Yanille]] - [[fairy ring]] code: {{Fairycode|CLS}}. You may also use the [[minigame teleport]] for [[Nightmare Zone]] or the [[Fishing Trawler]], a [[Watchtower]]/Yanille teleport, the [[Ardougne cloak]] [[Ardougne Monastery|Monastery]] teleport and run south-east, the [[Castle Wars]] teleport using a [[ring of dueling]] then running east. If teleportation is to no avail, another manual option is to Charter a boat in Brimhaven to Port Khazard then run south passing the Fight Arena and head to the east of Yanille where the small island should be located.
*Talk to [[Hazelmere]], he will take your Bark sample and give you a [[Hazelmere's scroll|message]].
}}

===Glough===
{{Map|x=2477|y=3463|r=3|width=250|height=250|mtype=square|align=right|caption=Glough's house location.}}
{{Checklist|
*Return to [[King Shareen]]. He will ask what the message says. Tell him: {{Chat option|1I think so.|5None of the above.|5None of the above.|2A man came to me with the King's seal.|1I gave the man Daconia rocks.|4And Daconia rocks will kill the tree!}}
*Head south. At the bottom of the ramp, turn east and go up the ladder to speak with [[Glough]].
}}

===Investigation===
{{Needed|1000 [[coins]] (if you haven't helped [[Femi]])|recommended=A [[teleport]] out of [[Karamja]].}}
{{Checklist|*Return to [[King Shareen]], and he will tell you that [[Glough]] has caught a human. Ask to see the prisoner.
*Talk to the prisoner [[Charlie]] on the top floor of the grand tree. '''Make sure to finish the entire conversation!'''
*Go to Glough's house. Search the cupboard, and you will find his journal.
*Talk to Glough and wait to be arrested.
*Talk to Charlie, he will tell you about the [[Shipyard]] on [[Karamja]], the password is '''Ka-Lu-Min'''.
*[[King Shareen|The king]] appears and tells you to escape using the [[Gnome glider]] on top of the tree.
*Travel with the glider.}}

===Karamja===
{{Checklist|
*The glider will crash near the [[Ship Yard]]. Run east past the level 53 [[jogre]]s to the [[Ship Yard]] gate.
*Open the gate and tell the [[Shipyard worker|worker]] Glough sent you, then give the password '''Ka-Lu-Min'''. {{Chat option|2Glough sent me.|1Ka.|2Lu.|2Min.}}
*Find the [[Foreman]] on the southern dock. Kill him or talk to him to get a [[Lumber order]].
**If you talk to him, he will ask you some security questions. {{Chat option|3Sadly his wife is no longer with us!|2He loves worm holes.|1Anita.}}
*Take the [[Lumber order]] to [[King Shareen|the king]]. (Teleport into the stronghold or get [[Femi]] to sneak you in, costing 1,000 coins if you didn't help her earlier). The king will not believe you when you show him the Lumber order.
}}

===Tuzo===
{{Map|x=2391|y=3511|r=3|width=250|height=250|align=right|caption=Anita's house on the map.|mtype=square}}
{{Needed|[[Lumber order]].}}
{{Checklist|
*Speak to [[Charlie (prisoner)|Charlie]] again on the top floor of the [[Grand Tree]].
*Speak to [[Anita]] up the stairs west of the swamp, north-west of the Grand Tree. She will give you a [[Glough's key|key]]. {{Chat option|1}}
*Go to Glough's house, and use the key to open the chest and take the [[invasion plans]]. '''Make sure to complete the dialogue window to receive the plans!'''
*Take the invasion plans to the king. He will give you four letters made of sticks (you'll need 4 empty inventory spaces).
*Climb the watchtower in Glough's house (tree in east part of his house). Use the sticks with the four pillars to spell out '''TUZO'''. If you are under 25 [[Agility]] eat your [[summer pie]] now.
*Bank if needed and prepare for the battle, then go down the trapdoor.
}}

===Encountering the Black demon===
{{Needed|[[Combat]] [[equipment]] and [[food]] to last in a fight against a level 172 [[Black demon]].}}
[[File:Black demon (The Grand Tree, 1) safespot.png|thumb|'''Safespot 1:''' A far safer and more reliable safespot.]]
[[File:Black demon (The Grand Tree, 2) safespot.png|thumb|'''Safespot 2:''' The safespot where Glough stands. Not recommended to use.]]
{{Checklist|
*After you enter and talk to Glough, a level 172 [[Black demon]] will appear and attack you.
**Immediately after the cutscene ends, run to the tile directly north of the ladder. The [[Black demon]] will become stuck behind the mithril rocks in front of you as he approaches. Attack with Ranged, Magic, or a halberd.
**'''Warning:''' The demon will despawn after a while if it is not killed within 10 minutes exactly. If this happens, you'll have to exit through the ladder in the centre of the cave and go through Glough's trapdoor again.
*Kill the demon, walk along the passage until you find [[King Shareen]] standing by a ladder.
*Talk to the king and he will ask you to locate the last [[Daconia stone]]. ''Fully complete the dialogue otherwise you cannot continue.''
*Search the roots until you find it (make sure to click continue on the dialogue when you find the stone).
*Talk to the king one last time.
}}
'''Quest complete!'''

